The paper deals with channel estimation for wireless communication systems, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) categories. The use of closed-loop feedback to design sounding vectors and optimize beamforming gain involves system control and optimization, which could also place the paper in the systems and control (cs.SY) category. The paper also deals with massive MIMO, which involves large-scale data processing and machine learning, potentially placing it in the multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories.
